00:11:40.524 --> 00:11:42.976
Has anybody here seen that film? Yeah.

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:45.608
Remember when they threw
the Coke out of the airplane,

00:11:45.632 --> 00:11:47.960
and it landed on the ground,
and it didn't break?

00:11:47.984 --> 00:11:50.308
Now, see, that's because
Coke bottles are solid.

00:11:50.846 --> 00:11:54.133
It's nearly impossible
to break a Coke bottle.

00:11:54.157 --> 00:11:55.554
Do you want to try it?

00:11:57.269 --> 00:11:59.675
Good job. She's not taking any chances.

00:11:59.699 --> 00:12:00.976
(Laughter)

00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:03.381
You see, psychokinesis
is the paranormal influence

00:12:03.405 --> 00:12:05.888
of the mind on physical
events and processes.

00:12:06.382 --> 00:12:07.976
For some magicians or mentalists,

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:11.976
sometimes the spoon will bend
or melt, sometimes it will not.

00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:15.484
Sometimes the object will slide
across the table, sometimes it will not.

00:12:15.508 --> 00:12:17.780
It depends on how much
energy you have that day,

00:12:17.804 --> 00:12:18.868
so on and so forth.

00:12:18.892 --> 00:12:21.750
We're going to try an experiment
in psychokinesis, right now.

00:12:21.774 --> 00:12:23.903
Come right over here, next to me.
Excellent.

00:12:23.927 --> 00:12:25.712
Now, have a look at the Coke bottle.

00:12:25.736 --> 00:12:29.308
Make sure it is solid, there's only
one hole, and it's a normal Coke bottle.

00:12:29.332 --> 00:12:32.333
And you can whack it against the table,
if you want; be careful.

00:12:32.357 --> 00:12:34.357
Even though it's solid, I'm standing away.

00:12:34.381 --> 00:12:37.731
I want you to pinch right here
with two fingers and your thumb.

00:12:37.755 --> 00:12:40.309
Excellent.
Now, I've got a shard of glass here, OK.

00:12:40.333 --> 00:12:42.286
I want you to examine the shard of glass.

00:12:42.310 --> 00:12:44.885
Careful, it's sharp.
Just hold on to it for a moment.

00:12:44.909 --> 00:12:46.076
Now, hold it out here.

00:12:46.101 --> 00:12:50.001
I want you to imagine, right now,
a broken relationship from many years ago.

00:12:50.547 --> 00:12:53.628
I want you to imagine
all the negative energy

00:12:53.652 --> 00:12:55.804
from that broken
relationship, from that guy,

00:12:55.828 --> 00:12:58.332
being imparted into the broken
piece of glass,

00:12:58.356 --> 00:12:59.976
which will represent him, OK.

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:02.048
But I want you to take this
very seriously.

00:13:02.072 --> 00:13:04.358
Stare at the glass,
ignore everybody right here.

00:13:04.382 --> 00:13:07.505
In a moment, you'll feel
a certain sensation, OK,

00:13:07.529 --> 00:13:09.345
and when you feel that sensation,

00:13:09.369 --> 00:13:11.976
I want you to drop the piece
of glass into the bottle.

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:16.897
Think of that guy, that ba -- that guy.

00:13:16.921 --> 00:13:17.976
(Laughter)

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:19.413
I'm trying to be good here.

00:13:19.437 --> 00:13:21.247
OK, and when you feel the sensation --

00:13:21.271 --> 00:13:23.530
it might take a while --
drop it into the glass.

00:13:35.809 --> 00:13:36.809
OK, drop it in.

00:13:37.341 --> 00:13:39.976
Now, imagine all that negative
energy in there.

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:42.633
Imagine his name
and imagine him inside the glass.

00:13:42.657 --> 00:13:44.901
And I want you to release
that negative energy

00:13:44.925 --> 00:13:46.449
by shaking it from side to side.

00:13:47.566 --> 00:13:48.567
(Burst)

00:13:48.591 --> 00:13:50.976
(Laughter)

00:13:51.000 --> 00:13:53.532
That was a lot of negative energy,
built up in there.

00:13:53.556 --> 00:13:55.618
(Laughter)

00:13:55.642 --> 00:13:58.976
(Applause)

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:02.001
I also want you to look at me
and think of his name.

00:14:02.025 --> 00:14:06.000
OK, think of how many letters
in the title of his name.

00:14:06.024 --> 00:14:07.706
There's five letters in the title.

00:14:07.730 --> 00:14:09.977
You didn't react to that,
so it's four letters.

00:14:10.001 --> 00:14:11.976
Think of one of the letters in the title.

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:13.976
There's a K in his name, there is a K.

00:14:14.000 --> 00:14:16.376
I knew that because my name
starts with a K also,

00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:19.237
but his name doesn't start
with a K, it starts with an M.

00:14:19.261 --> 00:14:21.683
Tell Mike I said hello,
the next time you see him.

00:14:21.707 --> 00:14:23.376
Was that his name?
Nicole: Mm-hmm.

00:14:23.400 --> 00:14:25.177
KB: OK, give her a round of applause.

00:14:25.201 --> 00:14:30.809
(Applause)

00:14:30.833 --> 00:14:31.976
Thank you.

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:33.958
(Applause)

00:14:37.169 --> 00:14:38.468
(Applause ends)

00:14:38.492 --> 00:14:40.976
I've got one more thing
to share with you right now.

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:43.381
Actually, Chris, I was going
to pick you for this,

00:14:43.405 --> 00:14:45.644
but instead of picking you,
can you hop up here

00:14:45.668 --> 00:14:47.976
and pick a victim
for this next experiment?

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:50.572
And it should be a male victim,
that's the only thing.

00:14:50.596 --> 00:14:51.976
Chris Anderson: Oh, OK.

00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:53.386
KB: I was going to use you,

00:14:53.410 --> 00:14:55.976
but I decided I might want
to come back another year.

00:14:56.000 --> 00:14:57.015
(Laughter)

00:14:57.039 --> 00:14:59.151
CA: Well, to reward him
for saying "eureka,"

00:14:59.175 --> 00:15:02.743
and for selecting Michael Mercil to come
and talk to us -- Steve Jurvetson.

00:15:02.767 --> 00:15:04.513
KB: OK, Steve, come on up here.

00:15:04.537 --> 00:15:05.609
(Applause)

00:15:05.633 --> 00:15:06.674
CA: You knew!

00:15:06.698 --> 00:15:11.000
KB: OK, Steve, I want you to take
a seat, right behind here. Excellent.

00:15:12.689 --> 00:15:14.976
Now, Steve -- oh, you
can check underneath.

00:15:16.800 --> 00:15:19.363
Go ahead, I've no fancy
assistants underneath there.

00:15:19.387 --> 00:15:21.902
They insist that because I was a magician,

00:15:21.926 --> 00:15:23.466
put a nice, black tablecloth on.

00:15:23.490 --> 00:15:24.903
There you are, OK.

00:15:24.927 --> 00:15:25.976
(Laughter)

00:15:26.000 --> 00:15:27.976
I've got four wooden plinths here, Steve.

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:30.976
One, two, three and four.

00:15:31.000 --> 00:15:33.239
Now, they're all the exact
same except this one

00:15:33.263 --> 00:15:35.978
obviously has a stainless steel
spike sticking out of it.

00:15:36.002 --> 00:15:38.467
I want you to examine it,
and make sure it's solid.

00:15:41.095 --> 00:15:42.102
Happy?

00:15:42.126 --> 00:15:44.080
Steve Jurvetson: Mmm, yes.

00:15:44.104 --> 00:15:47.611
KB: OK. Now, Steve, I'm going
to stand in front of the table,

00:15:47.635 --> 00:15:49.407
When I stand in front of the table,

00:15:49.431 --> 00:15:51.546
I want you to put the cups on the plinths,

00:15:51.570 --> 00:15:53.809
in any order you want,
and then mix them all up,

00:15:53.833 --> 00:15:56.604
so nobody has any idea where
the spike is, all right?

00:15:56.628 --> 00:15:57.976
SJ: No one in the audience?

00:15:58.000 --> 00:15:59.976
KB: Yes, and just to help you out,

00:16:00.000 --> 00:16:02.986
I'll block them from view,
so nobody can see what you're doing.

00:16:03.010 --> 00:16:05.582
I'll also look away. So, go
ahead and mix them up, now.

00:16:05.606 --> 00:16:07.282
OK, and tell me when you're done.

00:16:09.933 --> 00:16:11.916
(Laughter)

00:16:12.710 --> 00:16:15.170
(Laughter)

00:16:16.572 --> 00:16:18.572
KB: You done?
SJ: Almost.

00:16:18.596 --> 00:16:21.533
KB: Almost, oh. OK, you're making
sure that's well hidden.

00:16:22.533 --> 00:16:26.976
Oh, we've got one here,
we've got one here.

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:29.976
(Applause)

00:16:30.000 --> 00:16:32.000
So, all right, we'll leave them like that.

00:16:32.024 --> 00:16:33.976
(Laughter)

00:16:34.000 --> 00:16:36.001
I'm going to have the last laugh, though.

00:16:36.025 --> 00:16:37.976
(Laughter)

00:16:38.000 --> 00:16:42.976
Now, Steve, you know where the spike is,
but nobody else, does? Correct?

00:16:43.000 --> 00:16:46.239
But I don't want you to know either,
so swivel around on your chair.

00:16:47.215 --> 00:16:50.263
They'll keep an eye on me
to make sure I don't do anything funny.

00:16:50.287 --> 00:16:52.334
No, stay around, OK.

00:16:58.876 --> 00:17:00.558
Now, Steve, look back.

00:17:00.582 --> 00:17:04.352
Now you don't know where the spike is,
and I don't know where it is either.

00:17:04.376 --> 00:17:06.843
Now, is there any way to see
through this blindfold?

00:17:07.522 --> 00:17:08.554
SJ: Put this on?

00:17:08.578 --> 00:17:11.325
KB: No, just, is there any way
to see through it? No?

00:17:11.349 --> 00:17:13.976
SJ: No, I can't see through it.
KB: Excellent.

00:17:14.000 --> 00:17:15.864
Now, I'm going to put on the blindfold.

00:17:15.888 --> 00:17:18.321
Don't stack them up, OK.
Give them an extra mix up.

00:17:18.345 --> 00:17:21.626
Don't move the cups, I don't want
anybody to see where the spike is,

00:17:21.650 --> 00:17:24.726
but give the plinths an extra mix up,
and then line them up.

00:17:24.750 --> 00:17:27.596
I'll put the blindfold on.
Give them an extra mix up.

00:17:27.620 --> 00:17:30.193
No messing around this time.
OK, go ahead, mix them up.

00:17:30.217 --> 00:17:32.217
My hand is at risk here.

00:17:34.976 --> 00:17:35.976
(Laughter)

00:17:36.000 --> 00:17:37.976
Tell me when you're done.
SJ: Done.

00:17:38.000 --> 00:17:40.976
KB: OK, where are you?
Put out your hand. Your right hand.

00:17:41.000 --> 00:17:42.976
Tell me when I'm over a cup.

00:17:43.000 --> 00:17:45.477
SJ: You're over a cup.
KB: I'm over a cup, right now?

00:17:45.501 --> 00:17:46.561
SJ: Mm-hmm.

00:17:46.585 --> 00:17:48.976
KB: Now, Steve, do you think
it's here? Yes or no?

00:17:49.000 --> 00:17:50.285
SJ: Oh!

00:17:50.309 --> 00:17:51.976
(Laughter)

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:53.976
KB: I told you I'd have the last laugh.

00:17:54.000 --> 00:17:58.871
(Laughter)

00:17:58.895 --> 00:18:02.370
SJ: I don't think it's there.
KB: No? Good decision.

00:18:02.394 --> 00:18:04.976
(Laughter)

00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:07.450
(Applause)

00:18:10.561 --> 00:18:11.976
(Applause ends)

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:14.572
Now, if I go this way,
is there another cup over here?

00:18:14.596 --> 00:18:15.976
SJ: Can we do the left hand?

00:18:16.000 --> 00:18:19.976
KB: Oh, no, no, no. He asked me could
he do the left hand. Absolutely not.

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:21.676
(Laughter)

00:18:21.700 --> 00:18:24.154
KB: If I go this way,
is there another cup?

00:18:24.178 --> 00:18:25.992
SJ: Yes.
KB: Tell me when to stop.

00:18:26.016 --> 00:18:27.134
SJ: OK.
KB: There?

00:18:27.158 --> 00:18:28.198
SJ: Yes, there's one.

00:18:28.222 --> 00:18:31.809
KB: OK. Do you think it's here, yes or no?
This is your decision, not mine.

00:18:31.833 --> 00:18:34.645
(Laughter)

00:18:35.658 --> 00:18:37.976
SJ: I'm going to say no.
KB: Good decision.

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:39.976
(Laughter)

00:18:40.000 --> 00:18:41.976
OK, give me both hands.

00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:45.792
Now, put them on both cups.

00:18:45.816 --> 00:18:49.442
Do you think the spike
is under your left or your right hand?

00:18:49.506 --> 00:18:50.976
SJ: Neither.

00:18:51.000 --> 00:18:52.976
KB: Neither, oh, OK.

00:18:53.000 --> 00:18:54.558
But if you were to guess.

00:18:54.582 --> 00:18:56.952
(Laughter)

00:18:56.976 --> 00:18:59.376
SJ: Under my right hand.
KB: Under your right hand?

00:18:59.400 --> 00:19:01.877
Now, remember, you made
all the decisions all along.

00:19:01.901 --> 00:19:03.536
Psychologists, figure this out.

00:19:03.560 --> 00:19:04.651
(SJ gasps)

00:19:04.675 --> 00:19:05.976
Have a look.

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:07.001
SJ: Oh!

00:19:07.025 --> 00:19:10.320
(Applause)

00:19:10.344 --> 00:19:12.344
KB: Thank you.

00:19:16.738 --> 00:19:18.976
(Applause ends)

00:19:19.000 --> 00:19:21.572
If anybody wants to see
some sleight of hand later on,

00:19:21.596 --> 00:19:22.976
I'll be outside.

00:19:23.000 --> 00:19:24.094
Thank you.

00:19:24.118 --> 00:19:25.793
(Applause)

00:19:25.817 --> 00:19:27.794
Thank you.

00:19:27.818 --> 00:19:28.976
Thank you.

00:19:29.000 --> 00:19:32.000
(Applause)

